  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9c\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d8b\u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8 \u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db0\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Running at maximum capacity from Monday onwards",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A senior officer of the Ceylon Transport Board said that since the shortage of tires and batteries faced by the Ceylon Transport Board (Langama) is over, the buses will run at maximum capacity from next Monday.",
        "The official said that due to the lack of tires and batteries that Langama was facing, about 2,000 buses out of 5,000 buses were not able to run and thus about 80 percent of long-distance services had to be suspended.",
        "The official further said that the purchase was delayed due to a problem in the procurement process for the purchase of tires and batteries."
      ],
